If one or more tokens would be created under your control, twice that many of those tokens are created instead.

data.name: Ambassador Laquatus
data.oracle_text: {3}: Target player mills three cards.
data.flavor_text: "Life is a game. The only thing that matters is whether you're a pawn or a player."

data.name: Araumi of the Dead Tide
data.oracle_text: {T}, Exile cards from your graveyard equal to the number of opponents you have: Target creature card in your graveyard gains encore until end of turn. The encore cost is equal to its mana cost. (Exile the creature card and pay its mana cost: For each opponent, create a token copy that attacks that opponent this turn if able. They gain haste. Sacrifice them at the beginning of the next end step. Activate only as a sorcery.)

data.name: Dalakos, Crafter of Wonders
data.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}{C}. Spend this mana only to cast artifact spells or activate abilities of artifacts.
Equipped creatures you control have flying and haste.
data.flavor_text: His imagination soars from the depths of the sea to the heights of the heavens.

data.name: Empress Galina
data.oracle_text: {U}{U}, {T}: Gain control of target legendary permanent. (This effect lasts indefinitely.)
data.flavor_text: "Above the waves you may be mighty indeed, but down here you belong to me."

data.name: Emry, Lurker of the Loch
data.oracle_text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each artifact you control.
When Emry, Lurker of the Loch enters the battlefield, mill four cards.
{T}: Choose target artifact card in your graveyard. You may cast that card this turn. (You still pay its costs. Timing rules still apply.)

data.name: Jori En, Ruin Diver
data.oracle_text: Whenever you cast your second spell each turn, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: "Some relic hunters have given up exploring and gone to fight the Eldrazi. But I know our work is more important than ever. The secrets we uncover could lead to the world's salvation."

data.name: Kopala, Warden of Waves
data.oracle_text:
Spells your opponents cast that target a Merfolk you control cost {2} more to cast.
Abilities your opponents activate that target a Merfolk you control cost {2} more to activate.
data.flavor_text: "I know these waters better than you know yourselves."

data.name: Kumena, Tyrant of Orazca
data.oracle_text:
Tap another untapped Merfolk you control: Kumena, Tyrant of Orazca can't be blocked this turn.
Tap three untapped Merfolk you control: Draw a card.
Tap five untapped Merfolk you control: Put a +1/+1 counter on each Merfolk you control.

data.name: Noyan Dar, Roil Shaper
data.oracle_text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, you may put three +1/+1 counters on target land you control. If you do, that land becomes a 0/0 Elemental creature with haste that's still a land.
data.flavor_text: After many years as a lullmage, Noyan Dar turned his talents from allaying Zendikar's fury to the considerably easier task of rousing it.

data.name: Prime Speaker Zegana
data.oracle_text:
Prime Speaker Zegana enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it, where X is the greatest power among other creatures you control.
When Prime Speaker Zegana enters the battlefield, draw cards equal to its power.

data.name: Svyelun of Sea and Sky
data.oracle_text:
Svyelun of Sea and Sky has indestructible as long as you control at least two other Merfolk.
Whenever Svyelun attacks, draw a card.
Other Merfolk you control have ward {1}. (Whenever another Merfolk you control becomes the target of a spell or ability an opponent controls, counter it unless that player pays {1}.)

data.name: Sygg, River Cutthroat
data.oracle_text: At the beginning of each end step, if an opponent lost 3 or more life this turn, you may draw a card. (Damage causes loss of life.)
data.flavor_text: "It's not a matter of deserving. It's a matter of strength. The power to hold versus the power to take."

data.name: Sygg, River Guide
data.oracle_text:
Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
{1}{W}: Target Merfolk you control gains protection from the color of your choice until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: "If there's a place worth going, the Merrow Lanes already do. And if there's a route worth taking, yours truly already has."

data.name: Talrand, Sky Summoner
data.oracle_text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, create a 2/2 blue Drake creature token with flying.
data.flavor_text: "The seas are vast, but the skies are even more so. Why be content with one kingdom when I can rule them both?"

data.name: Tatyova, Benthic Druid
data.oracle_text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you gain 1 life and draw a card.
data.flavor_text: "Yavimaya is one being—one vastness of rippling leaves, one deepness of roots, and one chatter of animals—of which I am one part."

data.name: Thada Adel, Acquisitor
data.oracle_text:
Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
Whenever Thada Adel, Acquisitor deals combat damage to a player, search that player's library for an artifact card and exile it. Then that player shuffles. Until end of turn, you may play that card.

data.name: Thrasios, Triton Hero
data.oracle_text:
{4}: Scry 1, then reveal the top card of your library. If it's a land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped. Otherwise, draw a card.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)
data.flavor_text: Beneath crashing waves lies an ocean of secrets waiting to be explored.

data.name: Tishana, Voice of Thunder
data.oracle_text:
Tishana, Voice of Thunder's power and toughness are each equal to the number of cards in your hand.
You have no maximum hand size.
When Tishana enters the battlefield, draw a card for each creature you control.

data.name: Tuvasa the Sunlit
data.oracle_text:
Tuvasa the Sunlit gets +1/+1 for each enchantment you control.
Whenever you cast your first enchantment spell each turn, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: "My people have always been here, and here we shall remain."

data.name: Vorel of the Hull Clade
data.oracle_text: {G}{U}, {T}: Double the number of each kind of counter on target artifact, creature, or land.
data.flavor_text: "I used to hurl rocks and eat scraps of meat burned over a fire. Look at what I've become and tell me Simic does not hold infinite possibility."
